metadata.name: PIPES #75
metadata.description:
PIPES are its own creatures growing out of an Octree, swirling and twirling towards each's individual destination.  

Features:   
  There are four different flow modes, seven different palettes.   
  PIPES can either be hollow or filled, and there is a small chance the PIPES is drawn in gradient.  

Loading time is about 6s and then it will start to animate. Thank you for your patience.  

Press 'S' to save a high resolution 4800x4800px PNG of the artwork.  

This work is made purely with p5js.

metadata.name: Modulation #99
metadata.description:
Isometric cityscapes, patterns and geometries generated by trigonometric functions and rendered as SVG.

The SVG can be saved by pressing "s" on the full-screen view.
A PNG version can be exported by pressing "e" on the full-screen view.

By default the dimensions of the export are 6000×7500.
These dimensions can be changed by adding, for example, ?w=12000 to the full-screen page URL, where w is the desired width. Then press "e" to export at this size.

metadata.name: Here, After #151
metadata.description:
We were all there
when the sky cried confetti
and if we weren’t, we felt like we had
but here, after
held with each other’s eyes
not much is said at all

——

A : Animate rendering
S : Save current resolution
1 -> 5 : Save low -> high resolution

metadata.name: Flow #192
metadata.description:
Flow is a collection of eye pleasing formula's in the form of patterns and colors.

Features include:
- Patterns
- Palettes
- Focus points
- Margins
- Sizes
- Spacings
- Color distribution patterns
- Modifiers
- Gradients
- Dots
- Overflow

Due to the large amount of calculations it may take a few seconds to generate.
The spinning indicator on the top right disappears when it is finished, this is the best moment to save.

Press [s] to save a high resolution PNG @ 9933x14043 pixels (A0 paper dimensions @ 300 DPI).

Flow By @OneDayOfCrypto, 2022

metadata.name: Euphonic #97
metadata.description:
Euphonic is an exploration of the emergent visual properties that arise from placing layers of simple lines atop one another.

In general this effect is called the Moiré effect. This effect really feels best in the tactile - when you have a printed page and an acetate sheet. This piece attempts to recreate that tactile joy.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.

Licensing: BY-NC-ND see license.md for details.

metadata.name: UPLOAD.EXE #162
metadata.description:
No death in the metaverse 
100 billion mortal coils before us, reduced to silly memes 

Here then, a chance to right every wrong 
Or curse ourselves, forgetting we once counted days so keenly 

C:\SOULS>UPLOAD.EXE -commit -purge 
Irreversible operation. Are you sure? [Y/N] Y_

Additional params 

&fullsize=true : 4096x4096 output 
&debug=true : Display generative figure outlines  
&notilt=true : Remove tilt-shift filter 


References 

How to draw a basic Human Figure Using Circles Only - Photoshop - Easy Anatomy Drawing Tutorial  
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TgIYpe4dPWo 


Libraries (refer licenses.js) 

pixijs/pixijs - Graphics 
bjornharrtell/jsts – Polygon routines 
meodai/poline - Colour routines 
jwagner/simplex-noise - Noise gen 
strainer/fdrandom - Random number gen

metadata.description:
This artwork celebrates the human brain, highlighting the vital role of neurons in facilitating information flow and coordinating brain functions. While we may occasionally forget things, the beauty lies in the fact that memories can be reactivated with a single line.

metadata.name: Morpho Gene #29
metadata.description:
This generative projects employs a vector field created by composing various functions based on a "genome".

Although I tried to expose only those parameters that collectors care about, there are a few things to keep in mind while playing with them: The "Manual genome" parameter is only considered when "Random genome" boolean is `false`. Also the genome can be composed only of lowercase and uppercase alphabetical letters.

An easy trick to find a genome on your liking is to first check the "Random genome" control while you use the randomize parameters. Once you found one, you can copy from features and paste it on "Manual genome" field and uncheck the random.

For the sake of feedback I included a small text bases progress indicator on the upper left corner. Also in the same corner I included a link that will start rendering higher version.

The resolution of the rendering is 1024 x 1024 / aspect ratio. The higher version is 4096 x 4096 / aspect ratio.

The 50% of royalties go to the minter.

Press 's' key to save a png.
Click on canvas to watch the rendering at 100% zoom factor.
Click it again to return to the scaled to fit the window.

metadata.name: Richter #109
metadata.description:
Richter is the second collaboration of Richard Nadler and Leander Herzog, following their first project called Gerhard. A generative animation based on multiple layers of color and data, mixed, moved and painted over in realtime. Some fragments stick to the canvas while others get discarded to leave the existing layers visible, allowing a complex surface to emerge and build up over time.
 
Richter works with data from 4 of 24 highres images, 30mb in total. This is the maximum size fxhash allows for a project and three times more than Gerhard. Richard Nadler created stunning new textures, enabling more variation in composition and detail to emerge at much higher resolution. Leander Herzog created the code for the interplay between the layers, motion and interactions. Richter elevates the approach from Gerhard with new methods for the realtime rendering process and new features like offline-first caching. Both artists use different tools and are not aware of the details of each others process, meeting through the interface of pixels as data.
 
Richter is featured in the exhibition "Generative Abstraction" at Expanded.art in Berlin.
 
- Click to start a new layer of motion and color.
- Doubleclick to enter fullscreen.
- Press “s” to save the canvas.
- Append ?dpr=4 to the url to increase the resolution.

leanderherzog.ch/2023/richter/
leanderherzog.ch/2022/gerhard/
fxhash.xyz/generative/17030/

metadata.name: Minimalist #31
metadata.description:
This abstract art is produced by exercising concepts of minimalism. Each artwork is composed of simple figures and simple engaging colors. 

Each abstract art piece is generated to connect with a specific type of person. When the viewer sees an abstract image that resonates with him or her a connection is made. 

This artwork was produced using computer graphics software and randomly layerd images.
